# Known bug signatures for crash deduplication (pquery-compatible format)
#
# Format: SIGNATURE  ## MDEV-XXXXX or comment
#   SIGNATURE is a pipe-separated string: [assertion|]SIGNAL|frame1|frame2|frame3|frame4
#
# Matching: fixed-string substring match (same as pquery's grep -F)
#
# To suppress a known crash, copy the signature line from:
#   crashes/seen_signatures.strings  or  crashes/crash_XXXX.sig
# into this file.
#
# Examples:
#   SIGABRT|Diagnostics_area::set_ok_status|mysql_insert  ## MDEV-12345
#   SIGSEGV|Field::check_assignability_from|Item::check_assignability_to  ## MDEV-34780
#   m_status == DA_ERROR|SIGABRT|THD::raise_condition  ## assertion crash
#
